result.execSummary:
The defendant Allen F Dorsey Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+) [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[MK] case called at 10:37am. 
Defendant Allen F Dorsey in court, in custody, with Attorney Karl E Huebner.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
ADA Hall verifies victim rights compliance; the victim impact statement is submitted.
Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited; plea of " No Contest " entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated;  the Court accepts the plea, finds Mr. Dorsey guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2.

On Count #1 the Court withholds sentence and places Mr. Dorsey on Probation for three years, with conditions:  
--to undergo assessment, treatment, and counseling as may be required by the Agent 
--to obtain/maintain employment or education program
--to comply with all Family Court Orders regarding child support
--to make all child support payments on time
--to make all payments on arrearages according to the Child Support orders

--to pay extradition fees
